HEADWORD: Incensed
<hw>In*censed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Angered; enraged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Represented as enraged, as any
wild creature depicted with fire issuing from mouth and eyes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incensement</ent>⟦br⟧
